<p>To protect Netlify from getting flooded by automated deploys or misbehav=
ing applications, the Netlify API is rate limited.</p>
<p>You can make up to 500 requests per minute for most requests.
Certain operations have their own stricter limits. For example, you can dep=
loy through the Netlify API up to 3 times per minute and up to 100 times pe=
r day.</p>
<p>You can check the returned HTTP headers of any API request to verify you=
r current rate limit status:</p>
