<p>The most common API action is doing deploys, either of a new site or an =
existing site. If <a href=3D"https://docs.netlify.com/build/configure-build=
s/stop-or-activate-builds">builds are stopped</a> for an existing site, you=
 can still deploy with the API to update the site.</p>
<p>Netlify supports two ways of doing deploys:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href=3D"https://docs.netlify.com/api-and-cli-guides/api-guides/get-s=
tarted-with-api#file-digest-method">Sending a digest</a> of all files in yo=
ur deploy, and then uploading any files Netlify doesn=E2=80=99t already hav=
e on its storage servers.</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://docs.netlify.com/api-and-cli-guides/api-guides/get-s=
tarted-with-api#zip-file-method">Sending a ZIP file</a> of the entire site =
and letting Netlify unzip and deploy.</li>
</ol>
<p>If you=E2=80=99re looking to deploy sites at scale, such as building an =
AI code agent and looking for a deploy target, check out the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://docs.netlify.com/extend/building-code-agents/apis-for-code-agents/#app=
">APIs for code agents docs</a>.</p>
<p>Whether you deploy a brand new site or create a deploy within an existin=
g site, the process is similar.</p>
<p>First <a href=3D"https://docs.netlify.com/api-and-cli-guides/api-guides/=
get-started-with-api#create-site">create a new site</a>, if needed:</p>
<div class=3D"expressive-code"><figure class=3D"frame not-content"><figcapt=
ion class=3D"header"></figcaption><pre data-language=3D"plaintext"><code><d=
iv class=3D"ec-line"><div class=3D"code"><span style=3D"--0:#a6accd">POST /=
api/v1/sites</span></div></div></code></pre><div class=3D"copy"><div aria-l=
ive=3D"polite"></div><button title=3D"Copy to clipboard" data-copied=3D"Cop=
ied!" data-code=3D"POST /api/v1/sites"><div></div></button></div></figure><=
/div>
<p>Now you have a site ID and you can create a new deploy, either with a <a=
 href=3D"https://docs.netlify.com/api-and-cli-guides/api-guides/get-started=
-with-api#file-digest-method">file digest</a> or a <a href=3D"https://docs.=
netlify.com/api-and-cli-guides/api-guides/get-started-with-api#zip-file-met=
hod">ZIP file</a>.</p>
<div class=3D"legacy-anchor" id=3D"deploying-via-files-digest"></div>
