<div class=3D"expressive-code"><figure class=3D"frame not-content"><figcapt=
ion class=3D"header"></figcaption><pre data-language=3D"plaintext"><code><d=
iv class=3D"ec-line"><div class=3D"code"><span style=3D"--0:#a6accd">GET /a=
pi/v1/sites/{site_id}/deploys/{deploy_id}</span></div></div></code></pre><d=
iv class=3D"copy"><div aria-live=3D"polite"></div><button title=3D"Copy to =
clipboard" data-copied=3D"Copied!" data-code=3D"GET /api/v1/sites/{site_id}=
/deploys/{deploy_id}"><div></div></button></div></figure></div>
<p>You can check the <code dir=3D"auto">state</code> parameter in the respo=
nse. It will be set to <code dir=3D"auto">preparing</code> as the upload ma=
nifest is generated, and either <code dir=3D"auto">prepared</code>, <code d=
ir=3D"auto">uploading</code>, <code dir=3D"auto">uploaded</code>, or <code =
dir=3D"auto">ready</code> depending on the contents of the deploy. At this =
point, the deploy is either <code dir=3D"auto">ready</code>, or the API wil=
l give you a list of <code dir=3D"auto">required</code> files and <code dir=
=3D"auto">required_functions</code>.</p>
<p>Additionally, when uploading large files, sometimes the request will tim=
e out. It is safe to retry these uploads a few times to verify whether addi=
tional attempts are successful.</p>
